Aim: program to estimate and subtract the background of an image 

Code :-  
% Read the input image  
originalImage = imread('beamer.jpg');  
% Convert the image to grayscale (if it's not already)  
grayImage = rgb2gray(originalImage);  
% Apply a threshold to segment the background  
threshold = 150;  
% Adjust the threshold value as needed  
binaryMask = grayImage < threshold;  
% Create a mask for the foreground (inverse of the background mask)  
foregroundMask = ~binaryMask;  
% Subtract the background by setting background pixels to zero  
backgroundSubtractedImage = originalImage;  
backgroundSubtractedImage(repmat(foregroundMask, [1, 1, 3])) = 0;  
% Display the original image and the background-subtracted image figure;  
subplot(1, 2, 1);  
imshow(originalImage);  
title('Original Image');  
subplot(1, 2, 2);  
imshow(backgroundSubtractedImage);  
title('Background-Subtracted Image');
